 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 4.14,
   "text": "In China, you can't order three beer, and the reason has nothing to do with alcohol,"
  },
  {
   "start": 4.46,
   "end": 5.1,
   "text": "but with grammar."
  },
  {
   "start": 5.64,
   "end": 8.16,
   "text": "In Chinese, you can't put a number straight onto a noun."
  },
  {
   "start": 8.74,
   "end": 11.62,
   "text": "No three beer, no two dog, no five book."
  },
  {
   "start": 12.08,
   "end": 15.42,
   "text": "Between the number and the thing, you need a measure word, a classifier."
  },
  {
   "start": 16.0,
   "end": 19.92,
   "text": "So three beers becomes literally three bottles beer, Sanping Pijou."
  },
  {
   "start": 20.4,
   "end": 22.82,
   "text": "That little ping, bottle, is the measure word."
  },
  {
   "start": 23.26,
   "end": 26.02,
   "text": "Leave it out, and it's broken Chinese, and it goes deeper."
  },
  {
   "start": 26.02,
   "end": 30.72,
   "text": "There are over 150 of these measure words, and which one you use depends on the shape"
  },
  {
   "start": 30.72,
   "end": 31.4,
   "text": "or type of thing."
  },
  {
   "start": 31.88,
   "end": 36.92,
   "text": "Flat things, long things, animals, books, machines, almost everything has its own."
  },
  {
   "start": 37.28,
   "end": 38.04,
   "text": "But here's the relief."
  },
  {
   "start": 38.36,
   "end": 41.94,
   "text": "One general measure word, G-I, works for the huge majority of cases."
  },
  {
   "start": 42.44,
   "end": 44.7,
   "text": "By some counts, around 94% of the time."
  },
  {
   "start": 45.2,
   "end": 47.92,
   "text": "So if you blank on the exact one, G will usually save you."
  },
  {
   "start": 48.32,
   "end": 49.86,
   "text": "Not always perfect, but understood."
  },
  {
   "start": 50.46,
   "end": 52.48,
   "text": "In English, three just works on everything."
  },
  {
   "start": 53.16,
   "end": 56.32,
   "text": "In Chinese, you have to know what kind of thing you're counting before you can"
  },
  {
   "start": 56.32,
   "end": 59.86,
   "text": "count it, which is why ordering three beers is secretly a grammar exam."
  },
  {
   "start": 60.38,
   "end": 61.78,
   "text": "Want to actually start learning Chinese?"
  },
  {
   "start": 62.4,
   "end": 66.48,
   "text": "Discover thousands of free exercises and more learning content on stacktags.io."
  }
